<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Parts_of_Speech">Parts of Speech</span></h2>
<p>These following grammar points fit pretty neatly into one part of speech category.
</p>
<h3><span class="mw-headline" id="Adverbs">Adverbs</span></h3>
<table class="wikitable" style="width:50em; text-align:left">

<tbody><tr>
<th>Grammar Point (English)</th>
<th>Pattern</th>
<th>Examples
</th></tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="ASGIRILI" class="mw-redirect" title="ASGIRILI">Continuation with "hai"</a></td>
<td>Subj. + 还 + Verb Phrase / Adj.</td>
<td><span class="liju">你 <em>还在</em> 看 书 ？</span>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="ASGY21RK" class="mw-redirect" title="ASGY21RK">Emphasis with "jiushi"</a></td>
<td>就是 + Verb</td>
<td><span class="liju">我 父母 <em>就是</em> 不 让 我 一个人 去 。</span>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="ASGWNEYM" class="mw-redirect" title="ASGWNEYM">Emphasizing quantity with "dou"</a></td>
<td>大家 / 很多人 + 都⋯⋯</td>
<td><span class="liju">很 多 地方 <em>都</em> 有 wifi。</span>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="ASG9B210" class="mw-redirect" title="ASG9B210">Expressing "about to" with "jiuyao"</a></td>
<td>还有 + Time Period + 就要 + Verb Phrase + 了</td>
<td><span class="liju"><em>还有</em> 五 天 <em>就要</em> 放假 <em>了</em> 。</span>
</td></tr>
<tr>
<td><a href="ASGIZQJ2" class="mw-redirect" title="ASGIZQJ2">Expressing "again" in the future with "zai"</a></td>
<td>再 + Verb</td>
<td><span class="liju">我 下 次 <em>再</em> 来。</span>
</td></tr>
<tr>
